      EXPERIMENT - 01
      
     DDL COMMANDS- CREATE 

QUESTION-1

Create a table EMPLOYEE have the
following fields (emp_id, name,city,dob,adhar_no)

ANSWER:

create table employee(emp_id int,name varchar(20),city varchar(30),dob date,aadhar_no int);

desc employee;
+-----------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field     | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+-----------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| emp_id    | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| name      | varchar(20) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| city      | varchar(30) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| dob       | date        | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| aadhar_no | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
+-----------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

QUESTION-2

Create a table STUDENT have the
fields(roll_no, name, age, address, gender)and add following constraints on it.

ANSWER:

create table student(roll_no int,name varchar(20),age int,address varchar(50),gender varchar(10));

desc student;
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field   | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| roll_no | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| name    | varchar(20) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| age     | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| address | varchar(50) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| gender  | varchar(10) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

2.1 Roll_no – Primary key

alter table student add constraint a1 primary key(roll_no);

desc student; 
                                 
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field   | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| roll_no | int(11)     | NO   | PRI | NULL    |       |
| name    | varchar(20) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| age     | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| address | varchar(50) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| gender  | varchar(10) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

2.2 Name – does not allow null values

alter table student modify name varchar(20) not null;

desc student;                                  
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field   | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| roll_no | int(11)     | NO   | PRI | NULL    |       |
| name    | varchar(20) | NO   |     | NULL    |       |
| age     | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| address | varchar(50) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| gender  | varchar(10) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

2.3 Age- must be in between (0-99), does
not allow null values

alter table student add check(age>0 and age<99);


alter table student modify age int not null;




2.4 Gender- default value is ‘m’

alter table student alter gender set default 'm';

desc student;
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field   | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| roll_no | int(11)     | NO   | PRI | NULL    |       |
| name    | varchar(20) | NO   |     | NULL    |       |
| age     | int(11)     | NO   |     | NULL    |       |
| address | varchar(50) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| gender  | varchar(10) | YES  |     | m       |       |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)



QUESTION-3

Create a temporary table STUDENT1 of
STUDENT relation.

ANSWER:

create temporary table student1 select * from student;

mysql> desc student1;
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field   | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| roll_no | int(11)     | NO   |     | NULL    |       |
| name    | varchar(20) | NO   |     | NULL    |       |
| age     | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| address | varchar(50) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| gender  | varchar(10) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
+---------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)



QUESTION-4

Create a duplicate table of EMPLOYEE.


ANSWER:

create table emp select * from employee;

mysql> desc emp;
+-----------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| Field     | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
+-----------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
| emp_id    | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| name      | varchar(20) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| city      | varchar(30) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| dob       | date        | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
| aadhar_no | int(11)     | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
+-----------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)


 

QUESTION-5


Create an INVOICE database and having
following tables.


